"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526128\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 09, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bmp1665702784591.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bmp1665702784591.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bmp1665702784591.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bmp1665702784591\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n Uniface 10: Changes in Command Line Switches\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"bmp1665702784591__unifacechanges_in_command_line_switches_7528\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Changes have been made to the functionality of some command line switches and sub-switches\n </p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">New Command Line Switches and Sub-switches</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1__entry__1\">\n Switch\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dkq1665702626173.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dkq1665702626173.html\" title=\"Specifies whether compiled module information is generated when compiling objects with a command line switch.\">/cmi</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1__entry__2\">\n Sub-switch that determines whether compiled module information is generated by the command line compiler.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cck1665702542032.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cck1665702542032.html\" title=\"The /genSql switch generates DBMS-specific SQL command scripts for preparing an application database or the Uniface Repository, including creating tables and enforcing referential integrity constraints in the database.\">/genSql</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1__entry__2\">\n Switch used to generate SQL command scripts for preparing application databases and the Uniface Repository.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bhc1665702625956.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bhc1665702625956.html\" title=\"Compile all the specified development objects, regardless of their purpose (Normal, Palettes, and Templates).\">/iap</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1__entry__2\">\n Specify whether to compile all development objects, regardless of their purpose (Normal, Palettes, and Templates).\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hsx1665702626834.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hsx1665702626834.html\">/ilv</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1__entry__2\"> Compile the specified components using the\n                     indicated severity level for the compiler message <code class=\"ph codeph\">1000 - #Include\n                           <var class=\"keyword varname\">IncludeScript</var> not found</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"twc1665702654010.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/twc1665702654010.html\" title=\"Compiles main development objects that are defined as palettes (Purpose = P), but does not generate runtime objects. Use it to ensure that palettes do not contain ProcScript syntax errors.\">/plt</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1__entry__2\">\n Sub-switch that compiles main development objects that are defined as palettes, but does not generate runtime objects.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fmo1665702653737.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fmo1665702653737.html\" title=\"Compiles main development objects that are defined as templates (Purpose = T), but does not generate runtime objects. Use it to ensure that templates do not contain ProcScript syntax errors.\">/tpl</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d107e1_d108e1_d109e1__entry__2\">\n Sub-switch that compiles main development objects that are defined as templates, but does not generate runtime objects.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d110e1_d111e1_d112e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Changed Command Line Switches and Sub-switches</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d110e1_d111e1_d112e1__entry__1\">\n Switch\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d110e1_d111e1_d112e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d110e1_d111e1_d112e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qcr1665702695577.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qcr1665702695577.html\" title=\"Copy one or more entity occurrences from a source database or XML file to another.\">/cpy</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d110e1_d111e1_d112e1__entry__2\"> It is not possible to use the Data Copy\n                     facilities such as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/cpy</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ude(\"copy\")</span>\n                     to import Repository data. Use the export and import functionality instead. <span class=\"ph\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wxi1665702696586.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wxi1665702696586.html\" title=\"Uniface enables you to copy and convert your application data to and from different formats, including XML files and other databases.\">Data Copy Facility</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zgi1665702697293.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zgi1665702697293.html\" title=\"The Uniface Repository is versioned to ensure that development object definitions cannot be corrupted with data that comes from an incompatible version of the Repository, or when a dictionary is opened with an incompatible IDE version.\">Repository Versioning</a></span>\n                     . </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d110e1_d111e1_d112e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xsn1665702696023.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xsn1665702696023.html\" title=\"Import an XML file containing Repository definitions exported from the Uniface Repository.\">/imp</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d110e1_d111e1_d112e1__entry__2\">\n It is not possible to use the Repository import facilities <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/imp</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ude(\"import\")</span> to import data created by the Data Copy facilities such as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/cpy</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$ude(\"copy\")</span>. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bkn1665702696297.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bkn1665702696297.html\" title=\"Uniface enables you to export and import your development object definitions by means of XML files, with built-in safeguards to prevent Repository corruption. If the data is compatible, it is transparently migrated to the current Repository structures.\">Export and Import Facilities</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d110e1_d111e1_d112e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"enc1665702653522.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/enc1665702653522.html\" title=\"Compile entity collection operations and occurrence operations.\">/ceo</a>\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uld1665702653667.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uld1665702653667.html\" title=\"Analyze modeled entities and create entity descriptors for entities that share the same model name.\">/con (and /anm)</a>\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ifp1665702626096.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ifp1665702626096.html\" title=\"Compile all components, including server pages, HTML forms, forms, reports, services, entity services, and session services.\">/cpt</a>\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rtz1665702626248.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rtz1665702626248.html\" title=\"Compile dynamic server pages.\">/dsp</a>\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ars1665702626915.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ars1665702626915.html\" title=\"Compile Uniface entity service components.\">/esv</a>\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fvm1665702627074.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fvm1665702627074.html\" title=\"Compile Uniface form components.\">/frm</a>\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kjb1665702652886.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kjb1665702652886.html\" title=\"Compile Uniface report components.\">/rpt</a>\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"umc1665702653094.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/umc1665702653094.html\" title=\"Compile Uniface session service components.\">/ssv</a>\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gku1665702653234.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gku1665702653234.html\" title=\"Compile Uniface service components.\">/svc</a>\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"prm1665702626469.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/prm1665702626469.html\" title=\"Compile static server pages.\">/usp</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d110e1_d111e1_d112e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">These command line switches now support the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/tpl</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/plt</span> sub-switches.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Command line switches that compile components also support <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/cmi</span>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d113e1_d114e1_d115e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 3. </span><span class=\"title\">Obsolete Command Line Switches</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d113e1_d114e1_d115e1__entry__1\">\n Switch\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d113e1_d114e1_d115e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d113e1_d114e1_d115e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/exe</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d113e1_d114e1_d115e1__entry__2\">\n Switch that was specific to the Development Environment. No longer supported.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d113e1_d114e1_d115e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ins</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d113e1_d114e1_d115e1__entry__2\">\n Switch used to import the meta dictionary in Uniface 9. In Uniface 10, you can import the <span class=\"ph filepath\">umeta.xml</span> as you would any other Uniface sources.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d113e1_d114e1_d115e1__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/rma</span>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/sym</span>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bmp1665702784591__table_d113e1_d114e1_d115e1__entry__2\"> The Uniface Deployment Environment (URMA) is no\n                     longer delivered with Uniface, so this switch is now obsolete. You can use the\n                     Uniface Resource Manager (<span class=\"ph filepath\">urm</span>) to do most of the tasks\n                     that <code class=\"ph codeph\">/rma</code>\n<p class=\"p\"> </p> handled. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fpl1665702658861.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fpl1665702658861.html\" title=\"Executable for the Uniface Resource Manager, a command line utility for creating and manipulating Uniface archive files and other resources, files and DBMS tables.\">urm</a>. <p class=\"p\">Cross-reference functionality is not (yet) implemented in Uniface 10,\n                        so the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/sym</span> is not supported.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526128\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526128\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface 10: Changes in Command Line Switches Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 09, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface 10: Changes in Command Line Switches Changes have been made to the functionality of some command line switches and sub-switches Table 1. New Command Line Switches and Sub-switches Switch Description /cmi Sub-switch that determines whether compiled module information is generated by the command line compiler. /genSql Switch used to generate SQL command scripts for preparing application databases and the Uniface Repository. /iap Specify whether to compile all development objects, regardless of their purpose (Normal, Palettes, and Templates). /ilv Compile the specified components using the indicated severity level for the compiler message 1000 - #Include IncludeScript not found /plt Sub-switch that compiles main development objects that are defined as palettes, but does not generate runtime objects. /tpl Sub-switch that compiles main development objects that are defined as templates, but does not generate runtime objects. Table 2. Changed Command Line Switches and Sub-switches Switch Description /cpy It is not possible to use the Data Copy facilities such as /cpy and $ude(\"copy\") to import Repository data. Use the export and import functionality instead. For more information, see Data Copy Facility and Repository Versioning . /imp It is not possible to use the Repository import facilities /imp and $ude(\"import\") to import data created by the Data Copy facilities such as /cpy and $ude(\"copy\") . For more information, see Export and Import Facilities /ceo /con (and /anm) /cpt /dsp /esv /frm /rpt /ssv /svc /usp These command line switches now support the /tpl and /plt sub-switches. Command line switches that compile components also support /cmi . Table 3. Obsolete Command Line Switches Switch Description /exe Switch that was specific to the Development Environment. No longer supported. /ins Switch used to import the meta dictionary in Uniface 9. In Uniface 10, you can import the umeta.xml as you would any other Uniface sources. /rma /sym The Uniface Deployment Environment (URMA) is no longer delivered with Uniface, so this switch is now obsolete. You can use the Uniface Resource Manager ( urm ) to do most of the tasks that /rma handled. For more information, see urm . Cross-reference functionality is not (yet) implemented in Uniface 10, so the /sym is not supported. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}